Tolle moras: ſemper nocuit differre paratis.

THe bleſſed Apoſtle Saint Peter ſaith, that Jeſus Christ, while he lived here on earth, went about, doing good; that is,

   Acts 10.38. not good to himſelf; for ſo all worldlings, and all ambitious men go about continually, to do themſelves, that which they conceive to be good; but he went about to do good to all others, as ſtrengthening the feeble, comforting the broken hearted, and healing all that were oppreſſed of the devil; and as Saint Matthew ſaith, he gave ſight to the blinde, he cleanſed the leapers, and raiſed the dead;
Mat. 11.5. all good deeds indeed:


